WEBVTT

01:40.700 --> 01:44.690
<i>As a maid, one must rise 
with the sound of birds...</i>

01:45.630 --> 01:50.580
<i>and clean, even the places no one can see.</i>

01:52.710 --> 01:56.290
<i>Even if it's just a small apartment 
tucked away in a corner of Japan.</i>

01:57.330 --> 01:58.280
All right!

02:07.120 --> 02:09.260
<i>Did I lock up?</i>

02:13.720 --> 02:15.320
<i>I did!</i>

02:23.580 --> 02:27.080
CHYUN GUIDE
ALL OF JAPAN

02:23.580 --> 02:27.080
Let's see... It should be around here.

02:31.450 --> 02:32.720
<i>There it is!</i>

02:32.720 --> 02:35.220
<b>TAIYAKI</b>

02:33.810 --> 02:37.970
<i>According to the guidebook, 
sea bream is eaten on special occasions.</i>

02:40.690 --> 02:41.890
Hello!

02:41.890 --> 02:43.130
A maid?

02:44.490 --> 02:46.510
I'd like one taiyaki, please.

02:46.510 --> 02:48.870
It'll take a little while...

02:48.870 --> 02:49.900
I'll wait!

02:55.260 --> 02:58.410
<i>I wonder how Master is doing...</i>

02:58.710 --> 03:01.410
YESTERDAY

03:05.580 --> 03:10.750
<i>I haven't been to Japan since I was 
little, so I don't remember a thing.</i>

03:10.750 --> 03:12.640
<i>I'm a bit nervous.</i>

03:15.470 --> 03:17.260
Hello, this is Suzume.

03:18.380 --> 03:20.550
Yes, I've arrived safely.

03:20.840 --> 03:23.180
How are things over there?

03:26.150 --> 03:28.940
Master? Is something wrong?

03:29.260 --> 03:32.940
<i>Suzume, I need you
 to stay calm and listen.</i>

03:33.370 --> 03:39.070
<i>The mansion has collapsed, so I want 
you to stay in Japan for a while.</i>

03:39.390 --> 03:40.830
It's collapsed?

03:40.830 --> 03:44.510
<i>Yes. The plan was to build 
a rooftop pool...</i>

03:44.510 --> 03:46.850
<i>Anyway, we're lucky no one was injured.</i>

03:46.850 --> 03:49.990
<i>They said it'll take a year 
to rebuild, but don't worry.</i>

03:49.990 --> 03:51.590
<i>Suzume, are you there?</i>

03:58.150 --> 04:01.100
EEK!

03:58.880 --> 04:01.100
Just thinking about it 
gives me the chills!

04:01.740 --> 04:05.400
<i>This was supposed to be a short vacation.</i>

04:05.400 --> 04:07.600
<i>I never expected it to turn out like this.</i>

04:08.140 --> 04:11.050
<i>I've got no choice but to make 
my own way here for about a year</i>

04:11.050 --> 04:13.610
<i>while the mansion is being rebuilt.</i>

04:14.730 --> 04:16.810
Am I going to be okay?

04:17.610 --> 04:20.430
Miss! Your taiyaki is ready!

04:20.430 --> 04:21.370
Coming!

04:26.030 --> 04:27.970
<i>It really is shaped like a fish!</i>

04:27.970 --> 04:29.390
<i>How cute!</i>

04:29.390 --> 04:31.130
<i>It's adorable!</i>

04:31.130 --> 04:32.200
Now let's try it.

04:35.770 --> 04:37.130
When you eat taiyaki...

04:37.720 --> 04:40.170
is it okay to start with the head?

04:40.320 --> 04:42.530
MENACING...

04:42.530 --> 04:44.640
MENACING

04:47.000 --> 04:48.760
I'm going to start with the tail.

04:48.760 --> 04:49.970
Let's eat!

04:55.360 --> 04:57.760
<i>The thin, crispy crust 
with the red bean paste...</i>

04:57.760 --> 05:00.820
<i>It's just the right level of sweetness!</i>

05:02.360 --> 05:04.200
Wow, a maid.

05:05.470 --> 05:07.560
<i>That reminds me... The guidebook said</i>

05:07.560 --> 05:10.410
<i>that taiyaki comes in different varieties.</i>

05:14.080 --> 05:15.710
<i>Oh well!</i>

05:17.420 --> 05:21.090
Chyun! There are two 
main types of taiyaki!

05:21.350 --> 05:23.140
The first is "farmed" taiyaki.

05:23.140 --> 05:26.600
These are made with a large mold
that produces many at one time.

05:26.810 --> 05:29.550
Because it's difficult 
to control the heat,

05:29.550 --> 05:32.100
the result is usually 
a thick, chewy crust.

05:32.320 --> 05:34.220
The other kind is "wild-caught" taiyaki.

05:34.220 --> 05:37.110
With these, each fish is cooked
 by hand individually.

05:37.380 --> 05:40.710
The cook constantly flips the 
heavy mold to distribute the heat.

05:37.620 --> 05:43.110
ABOUT 2 KG

05:40.710 --> 05:43.110
It's difficult, time-consuming work...

05:43.770 --> 05:47.070
But it allows for precise 
heat control, resulting in taiyaki

05:47.070 --> 05:51.120
with a crispy crust and anko 
packed all the way to the tail!

05:51.400 --> 05:53.270
<i>I wonder which kind this is.</i>

05:53.270 --> 05:54.880
It's wild-caught!

05:54.880 --> 05:57.500
<i>The edges are especially crisp.</i>

05:57.500 --> 05:59.880
<i>I feel like they taste different.
They're delicious!</i>

06:00.190 --> 06:02.540
<i>The beans in the paste
 just melt in your mouth...</i>

06:02.540 --> 06:04.890
<i>It's so nice and warm!</i>

06:11.490 --> 06:13.890
All that's left is the head.

06:15.830 --> 06:19.400
MENACING

06:26.450 --> 06:27.920
<b>TAIYAKI</b>

06:26.450 --> 06:27.300
<b>TAIYAKI</b>

06:36.470 --> 06:38.130
That was delicious!

06:39.440 --> 06:42.840
Oh? The guidebook had 
instructions on how to eat it.

06:42.840 --> 06:47.210
Let's see... 
"How-You-Eat-Taiyaki Fortunes"?

06:47.210 --> 06:49.600
"If you start with the tail..."

06:50.140 --> 06:53.100
"You're a timid soul who can't 
quite take the first step."

06:54.850 --> 06:55.980
CHYUN GUIDE

06:56.280 --> 06:59.900
Master... I will try my very best!

07:20.500 --> 07:21.880
Grandma!

07:22.530 --> 07:23.880
Suzume!

07:24.640 --> 07:27.060
It's been too long, Grandma!

07:27.060 --> 07:30.010
It's great to see you here, Suzume. 
Have you been well?

07:30.010 --> 07:32.890
Yes! How is Grandpa?

07:33.110 --> 07:35.530
Disappointed he's missing seeing
his darling granddaughter

07:35.530 --> 07:39.020
today because he had 
some business to see to.

07:39.470 --> 07:42.150
Anyway, look at all that 
stuff you're carrying!

07:42.150 --> 07:44.110
These are all souvenirs for you, Grandma!

07:44.110 --> 07:45.320
All of them?!

07:45.600 --> 07:49.780
Rest assured, I shall carry them 
to your place for you!

07:49.780 --> 07:52.810
That's all right, dear.
 I'll be taking a taxi home.

07:53.900 --> 07:58.710
Since you've come all the way to Japan, 
I want you to accompany me today.

07:59.750 --> 08:01.590
Of course! I would love to!

08:01.590 --> 08:06.090
COIN LOCKERS

08:01.950 --> 08:04.060
First, let's stow all that in a locker.

08:04.060 --> 08:05.250
Okay...

08:15.110 --> 08:16.790
I couldn't resist after smelling it!

08:16.790 --> 08:19.220
Me too! It's just too good!

08:20.380 --> 08:21.410
Care to try some?

08:21.410 --> 08:22.360
Huh?

08:22.360 --> 08:25.130
I'm pretty sure it's 
around here somewhere...

08:25.130 --> 08:27.970
I've never had any before 
either, so I'm curious too.

08:29.100 --> 08:30.520
Be honest.

08:30.520 --> 08:31.770
I'd love to try it!

08:31.770 --> 08:32.870
Very well.

08:32.870 --> 08:35.120
<b>TAKO EBESU</b>

08:32.870 --> 08:35.120
<b>TAKOYAKI</b>

08:37.520 --> 08:38.790
This is amazing!

08:38.790 --> 08:40.370
We can watch them being made!

08:40.370 --> 08:41.500
Look, Grandma!

08:41.730 --> 08:44.270
I'd like an order of six 
with sauce and no aonori.

08:44.270 --> 08:46.580
And four toothpicks, please.

08:46.580 --> 08:48.910
Grandma, is this really your first time?

09:01.590 --> 09:03.120
Huh? What is that?

09:03.120 --> 09:04.770
It's a takoyaki pick.

09:14.700 --> 09:16.570
The balls formed like magic!

09:16.570 --> 09:18.510
Here comes the best part.

09:18.510 --> 09:20.830
Huh? What do you mean—

09:22.470 --> 09:23.410
Oil?

09:25.990 --> 09:28.720
The oil around the takoyaki 
is sizzling and popping...

09:29.170 --> 09:30.730
I-It can't be!

09:31.150 --> 09:32.680
That's right.

09:32.950 --> 09:36.060
By first cooking them until fluffy
and lightly frying them after,

09:36.060 --> 09:40.080
they achieve a crisp exterior 
with a soft, luscious inside!

09:40.080 --> 09:42.690
Grandma, you must be
 a regular here after all, right?!

09:46.450 --> 09:48.690
Look at the dancing bonito flakes!

09:48.690 --> 09:50.030
Let's eat!

09:50.030 --> 09:52.020
Suzume, you go first.

09:52.560 --> 09:53.950
Go on.

09:54.240 --> 09:55.470
Okay.

10:04.040 --> 10:05.180
So good!

10:05.180 --> 10:07.220
Suzume, let me show you something.

10:08.770 --> 10:10.630
<b>PERFECTLY
ROUND</b>

10:10.630 --> 10:13.010
Grandma, what is it that 
you're doing there?!

10:13.010 --> 10:14.790
Chyun! By using two toothpicks,

10:14.790 --> 10:20.630
you can maintain their perfectly 
round shape as you eat them!

10:20.630 --> 10:22.930
Me too! I want to try that too!

10:23.340 --> 10:25.020
Be careful, now. They're hot.

10:25.020 --> 10:25.900
Okay.

10:25.900 --> 10:30.400
<b>TAKO EBESU</b>

10:25.900 --> 10:30.400
<b>TAKOYAKI</b>

10:26.400 --> 10:27.650
Do you do it like this?

10:27.650 --> 10:29.300
Yes, just like that.

10:30.400 --> 10:33.400
<b>THAT WAS DELICIOUS!</b>

10:31.000 --> 10:32.940
That was delicious!

10:34.610 --> 10:36.410
My tummy feels warm.

10:36.760 --> 10:39.150
I'm glad to see you doing well.

10:39.150 --> 10:41.410
Do you think you'll be 
all right living in Japan?

10:41.970 --> 10:43.490
I think I'll be just fine!

10:43.490 --> 10:44.790
Be honest.

10:51.650 --> 10:54.220
Sure, I do have some worries.

10:54.460 --> 10:57.280
I've lived in the UK for so long.

10:58.030 --> 11:00.720
I'm also worried about the mansion...

11:05.660 --> 11:07.230
It'll be okay.

11:15.010 --> 11:17.780
You're my granddaughter, Suzume.

11:21.050 --> 11:23.840
If you find a good place, 
make sure you tell me all about it.

11:23.840 --> 11:25.100
Of course!

11:26.570 --> 11:30.050
<i>Master... There are things I'm 
concerned about, but for now,</i>

11:30.050 --> 11:33.060
<i>I'd like to enjoy living here 
the best I can!</i>

11:49.190 --> 11:52.900
Let's see. This one... and this one too.

11:53.690 --> 11:55.400
Okay! All set!

11:56.000 --> 11:57.450
<b>FULL</b>

11:57.730 --> 12:01.700
Suzume, if you find a good place, 
make sure you tell me all about it.

12:03.400 --> 12:05.950
I'm going to surprise Grandma with this!

12:10.930 --> 12:12.130
<i>Let's see.</i>

12:12.440 --> 12:14.970
<i>The seasonal hot spots are...</i>

12:19.110 --> 12:22.640
<i>Master, it's the height of spring
in Japan right now.</i>

12:23.960 --> 12:25.680
<i>The cherry blossoms are in full bloom!</i>

12:26.530 --> 12:28.670
Chyun! There are many varieties,

12:28.670 --> 12:32.650
but the one most commonly seen across 
Japan is called the Yoshino cherry.

12:32.940 --> 12:35.750
These Yoshino cherries 
are propagated as clones,

12:35.750 --> 12:37.900
so they share genes and growth times.

12:38.320 --> 12:40.040
When they explode into bloom

12:40.040 --> 12:42.730
varies based on temperature by region,

12:42.730 --> 12:46.410
which is how we can predict when 
they'll blossom in each area. Chyun!

12:46.940 --> 12:50.170
<i>It must be so cool 
to see it from outer space.</i>

12:51.420 --> 12:52.170
ODANGO

12:51.420 --> 12:52.170
FRESH FRUIT

12:52.170 --> 12:53.420
<b>WE HAVE ODANGO</b>

12:52.170 --> 12:53.420
THEY'RE
DELICIOUS

12:55.670 --> 12:57.130
<i>Speaking of dango...</i>

12:57.130 --> 13:00.740
<i>There's a Japanese saying related to 
cherry blossoms: "dango over flowers."</i>

13:00.740 --> 13:03.180
<i>It means to choose
 the practical over the elegant.</i>

13:03.180 --> 13:05.260
<i>Flowers... Dango...</i>

13:05.260 --> 13:07.060
<i>Flowers... Dango...</i>

13:07.060 --> 13:09.180
<i>Dango... Oh!</i>

13:09.510 --> 13:12.440
<i>Aww! Dango, dango...</i>

13:13.940 --> 13:16.070
BIG SMILE

13:16.070 --> 13:18.210
BIG SMILE

13:20.090 --> 13:23.700
Pure white dango 
with brilliant golden sauce!

13:24.160 --> 13:25.450
Let's eat!

13:29.960 --> 13:33.710
<i>This sticky-sweet sauce with chewy, 
satisfyingly springy mochi...</i>

13:34.140 --> 13:36.350
<i>The lightly charred parts 
have a toasty aroma.</i>

13:36.350 --> 13:37.760
<i>I can't stop eating!</i>

13:42.280 --> 13:46.350
I wonder how you're supposed to eat 
the ones in the middle of the skewer...

13:46.350 --> 13:48.520
<i>Method 1: just chomp!</i>

13:48.360 --> 13:55.610
<b>DANGEROUS</b>

13:48.520 --> 13:49.530
<i>That's dangerous!</i>

13:50.780 --> 13:53.050
<i>Method 2: bite down, then pull!</i>

13:52.870 --> 13:55.610
<b>WILD</b>

13:53.050 --> 13:54.050
<i>How wild!</i>

13:56.140 --> 13:58.320
Does the <i>Chyun Guide</i> say?

13:58.320 --> 13:59.870
Leave this to me, Chyun!

13:59.870 --> 14:02.790
For formal occasions like tea 
ceremonies, proper etiquette says

14:02.790 --> 14:07.310
to use a skewer or pick to remove
 the dango from the stick before eating.

14:07.310 --> 14:08.890
But if it's not a formal setting...

14:08.890 --> 14:11.580
First eat a third from one side,

14:11.950 --> 14:15.970
then turn it over so you
 can get to the rest.

14:17.310 --> 14:19.450
This way, you can eat it all neatly!

14:31.640 --> 14:33.170
<i>Dango over flowers, huh?</i>

14:33.680 --> 14:35.240
<i>This may be selfish of me...</i>

14:36.310 --> 14:40.030
<i>But I like having cherry 
blossoms and dango together!</i>

14:42.030 --> 14:46.690
By the way, if you take more than 
a third in the first bite...

14:47.100 --> 14:49.080
They can fall apart, so be careful!

14:50.330 --> 14:52.830
<b>THAT WAS DELICIOUS.</b>

14:52.830 --> 14:56.830
convenience store

14:52.830 --> 14:56.830
<b>SALTED RED SALMON</b>

14:52.830 --> 14:56.830
<b>CHICKEN AND MIXED RICE</b>

15:00.690 --> 15:03.440
<i>I've run out of the food 
I brought from the UK,</i>

15:03.440 --> 15:06.340
<i>so I tried to prepare breakfast at home.</i>

15:06.560 --> 15:10.350
<i>Except I had no idea I wouldn't 
be able to use the stove right away!</i>

15:10.350 --> 15:12.450
<i>But even on days like this...</i>

15:12.450 --> 15:13.850
They're open bright and early!

15:13.850 --> 15:18.360
<b>WET WIPES</b>

15:13.910 --> 15:18.360
<b>SALTED RED SALMON</b>

15:13.910 --> 15:18.360
<b>CHICKEN AND MIXED RICE</b>

15:14.970 --> 15:17.030
You can buy onigiri 
and wet wipes in one stop!

15:17.030 --> 15:18.360
Japan is incredible!

15:18.750 --> 15:20.060
First, let's try...

15:21.770 --> 15:22.960
Chicken and mixed rice!

15:23.360 --> 15:24.760
<i>Oh, wait.</i>

15:24.760 --> 15:28.110
<i>I need to clean my hands 
with the wipes first.</i>

15:28.110 --> 15:29.490
Now let's eat!

15:34.380 --> 15:37.510
<i>Chicken, burdock root, bamboo 
shoot, carrot, shiitake...</i>

15:37.510 --> 15:39.880
<i>The texture is delightful!</i>

15:40.370 --> 15:44.880
<i>The moist seaweed pairs really well 
and accents the flavors nicely.</i>

15:45.610 --> 15:47.230
Delicious!

15:47.760 --> 15:49.250
Next up...

15:49.760 --> 15:51.640
<b>SALTED RED SALMON</b>

15:50.070 --> 15:51.640
<b>SALMON</b>

15:50.110 --> 15:51.640
The salmon!

15:55.400 --> 15:56.640
<i>How do I open this?</i>

15:58.510 --> 16:00.400
Oh! It says on the bottom.

16:02.020 --> 16:03.400
Hey, this is fun.

16:05.820 --> 16:07.400
I did it!

16:06.880 --> 16:08.570
MESSY...

16:08.790 --> 16:09.660
Now then...

16:11.040 --> 16:14.700
<i>The seaweed is crispy! 
Completely different from earlier!</i>

16:14.700 --> 16:17.770
<i>I see... Since it's wrapped 
right before eating it,</i>

16:17.770 --> 16:20.710
<i>the seaweed doesn't get 
moist from the rice.</i>

16:20.710 --> 16:23.730
<b>SALTED RED SALMON</b>

16:20.710 --> 16:21.670
Chyun!

16:21.670 --> 16:24.390
This wrapper is called cut-tape packaging.

16:24.390 --> 16:29.970
It was developed in 1986 and 
revolutionized the onigiri world!

16:30.200 --> 16:33.140
<i>The rice in this one 
is tightly packed, too!</i>

16:33.140 --> 16:36.470
<i>The salmon is salted beautifully,
so it goes great with the white rice!</i>

16:36.920 --> 16:40.120
<i>I'll use the rest of the seaweed that 
was left in the wrapper somehow.</i>

16:40.120 --> 16:41.480
Right...

16:46.440 --> 16:51.490
By the way, if you peel off the ingredient
 label first, it'll open more cleanly!

16:51.490 --> 16:54.490
<b>THAT WAS DELICIOUS!</b>

16:52.390 --> 16:54.050
That was delicious!

16:55.170 --> 16:59.260
<i>When breakfast is delicious, it feels 
like the whole day will be wonderful.</i>

17:01.350 --> 17:02.830
<b>A</b>

17:01.370 --> 17:02.830
<i>A cat!</i>

17:01.970 --> 17:02.830
<b>CAT</b>

17:03.320 --> 17:05.840
<i>I've been blessed with 
a wonderful encounter!</i>

17:06.320 --> 17:08.320
<i>I... I want to pet it!</i>

17:08.880 --> 17:13.490
<i>But Grandma once told me 
I can't feed cats just anything.</i>

17:13.490 --> 17:15.850
<i>And I don't have any toys to play with...</i>

17:16.140 --> 17:17.950
<i>Oh, I've heard that with animals,</i>

17:17.950 --> 17:20.640
<i>it's best to get down on their eye level.</i>

17:21.100 --> 17:23.900
<i>I don't think anyone will see me
doing this at this hour.</i>

17:25.750 --> 17:28.110
<i>If I go to bed now, 
I can get three hours' shut-eye.</i>

17:28.440 --> 17:31.130
<i>Then I'll get back to work...</i>

17:36.620 --> 17:38.160
Here, kitty...

17:38.160 --> 17:40.340
Come here, come here.

17:39.870 --> 17:45.630
A CAT
A MAID

17:39.870 --> 17:45.630
ON THE GROUND
EARLY MORNING

17:40.340 --> 17:44.050
<i>A cat? A maid? On the ground?
 First thing in the morning?</i>

17:44.050 --> 17:45.630
<i>A cat...? And a maid...?</i>

17:50.750 --> 17:52.800
Excuse me... Pardon me...

18:04.880 --> 18:06.340
<i>I'm done for.</i>

18:07.820 --> 18:09.160
I didn't see her!

18:09.160 --> 18:10.640
And she's my neighbor!

18:10.640 --> 18:13.200
I missed my chance to introduce myself!

18:15.160 --> 18:17.900
I'm more tired than I thought...

18:17.900 --> 18:19.200
I better get to bed.

18:36.270 --> 18:37.930
<i>No matter how many times I check...</i>

18:38.400 --> 18:41.060
<i>There's a maid at my front door.</i>

18:43.130 --> 18:44.440
Yes?

18:44.440 --> 18:46.030
N-Nice to meet you!

18:46.030 --> 18:47.860
My name is Suzume Tachibana.

18:48.300 --> 18:51.570
I'm very sorry it took me this 
long to introduce myself.

18:52.030 --> 18:56.820
I come from the UK, and I'll be 
living here for about a year.

19:00.780 --> 19:02.650
It's a pleasure to finally meet you.

19:06.130 --> 19:07.320
H-Hello.

19:07.320 --> 19:12.570
Um... I'm sorry that you had to see me 
behaving so strangely the other day.

19:12.570 --> 19:14.590
<i>So it wasn't my imagination.</i>

19:14.590 --> 19:17.340
<b>JIICHIRO</b>

19:14.590 --> 19:17.340
So, if you'd like...

19:17.340 --> 19:18.970
Oh, baumkuchen.

19:18.970 --> 19:21.470
Oh, is that what this is?

19:26.210 --> 19:29.000
Just checking,
 but you got that for me, right?

19:29.000 --> 19:30.080
Oh, actually...

19:30.080 --> 19:31.730
I-I'm sorry.

19:31.730 --> 19:33.460
<b>JIICHIRO</b>

19:32.310 --> 19:35.810
I wasn't sure what to bring 
for this kind of thing.

19:35.810 --> 19:40.490
So I had my grandma prepare something 
for me and I just brought it...

19:48.560 --> 19:49.710
<i>She closed the door?!</i>

19:52.130 --> 19:53.920
I-I-I-I'm so sorry!

19:54.920 --> 19:56.800
<b>JIICHIRO</b>

19:57.070 --> 19:59.860
You've never had this 
baumkuchen before, right?

20:00.170 --> 20:01.690
Here, take one.

20:02.650 --> 20:04.920
Th-Thank you very much!

20:04.920 --> 20:05.810
Well, see you.

20:05.810 --> 20:08.940
Oh, excuse me! May I ask your name?

20:10.320 --> 20:11.940
It's Komatsu.

20:13.580 --> 20:16.950
<i>Oh yeah, I forgot to ask her
 about the maid outfit.</i>

20:17.330 --> 20:20.800
<i>Well, I guess that's just what you get 
when you do what you love</i>

20:20.800 --> 20:22.220
<i>and don't worry what others think.</i>

20:22.800 --> 20:25.780
Okay, time for some tea.

20:29.170 --> 20:30.080
Yes?

20:32.300 --> 20:34.340
It was delicious!

20:37.270 --> 20:39.970
I couldn't wait and opened it right away.

20:40.570 --> 20:42.100
Let's eat!

20:47.320 --> 20:49.920
It was fluffy! Oh, so fluffy!

20:49.920 --> 20:52.360
It was fluffy and moist at the same time!

20:52.360 --> 20:55.360
It also had a subtle and 
refined sweetness!

20:55.590 --> 20:57.410
The sugar on the outside
was nice and crunchy

20:57.410 --> 20:59.260
with a sweetness different from the cake,

20:59.260 --> 21:00.670
and they were even better together!

21:00.670 --> 21:02.660
Before I knew it,
 I'd eaten the whole thing!

21:03.870 --> 21:09.870
MENACING

21:07.200 --> 21:09.870
<i>Oh no. I think I might have messed up...</i>

21:14.700 --> 21:16.070
Hold on a sec!

21:16.070 --> 21:19.710
You ate it that fast and now you're 
giving me a review already?

21:19.710 --> 21:21.790
<i>Then what was that face for?</i>

21:21.790 --> 21:23.530
I was trying to keep cool, but you got me.

21:25.030 --> 21:26.850
My stomach hurts from laughing.

21:26.850 --> 21:29.720
That's the most I've used
 my facial muscles in a while.

21:31.440 --> 21:33.720
U-Um... Well...

21:32.070 --> 21:33.720
<i>What a weird girl.</i>

21:36.460 --> 21:37.400
It's Nana.

21:37.400 --> 21:39.150
Like the number seven in Japanese?

21:39.150 --> 21:42.010
That's my name. Nana Komatsu.

21:42.440 --> 21:44.410
I didn't give you my full name before.

21:44.680 --> 21:47.540
And... thanks for the gift.

21:49.390 --> 21:52.880
Suzume! I'm Suzume! Suzume Tachibana!

21:52.880 --> 21:54.210
You told me earlier...

21:54.210 --> 21:59.920
Baumkuchen is said to symbolize 
"layering happiness." Chyun!

21:54.620 --> 21:56.720
Do you want another one?

21:56.720 --> 21:59.920
Oh, no, that's okay! But if you insist...

23:30.620 --> 23:33.310
I love taking walks in Japan.
 They're so fun.

23:33.560 --> 23:35.600
I contemplate the cherry
 blossoms as they fall.

23:36.560 --> 23:39.340
That ice cream! Where are they selling it?
